<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="354" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,788]" box="[201,1361,476,501]" pageId="5" pageNumber="354">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,328,476,500]" pageId="5" pageNumber="354">Etymology</emphasis>
. The specific epithet is the genitive case of the species name, 
<taxonomicName box="[1023,1103,477,500]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Centaurea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="5" pageNumber="354" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="virgata">
<emphasis box="[1023,1103,477,500]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="354">virgata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, of the 
<typeStatus box="[1188,1236,477,501]" pageId="5" pageNumber="354">type</typeStatus>
host plant.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,788]" pageId="5" pageNumber="354">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,456,511,536]" pageId="5" pageNumber="354">Differential diagnosis</emphasis>
. The new species herein described has many similarities to 
<taxonomicName box="[1133,1340,512,536]" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Aceria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Prostigmata" pageId="5" pageNumber="354" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="squarrosae">
<emphasis box="[1133,1340,512,536]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="354">Aceria squarrosae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
de Lillo 
<emphasis box="[151,207,548,572]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="354">et al</emphasis>
. 
<number box="[227,286,548,572]" pageId="5" pageNumber="354" value="2003.0">2003</number>
, which was collected from 
<taxonomicName authority="Willd." authorityName="Willd." box="[625,953,548,572]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Centaurea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="5" pageNumber="354" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="squarrosa">
<emphasis box="[625,869,549,572]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="354">Centaurea squarrosa</emphasis>
Willd.
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[1001,1083,548,572]" name="Turkey" pageId="5" pageNumber="354">Turkey</collectingCountry>
. The Iranian species displays differences mainly in the prodorsal shield pattern which is characterized largely by having shorter median, admedian and submedian lines than those observed on 
<taxonomicName box="[778,936,620,644]" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Aceria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Prostigmata" pageId="5" pageNumber="354" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="squarrosae">
<emphasis box="[778,936,620,644]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="354">A. squarrosae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. No dashes are present between the median and admedian lines on the posterior half of the prodorsal shield in contrast with 
<taxonomicName box="[1062,1219,656,680]" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Aceria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Prostigmata" pageId="5" pageNumber="354" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="squarrosae">
<emphasis box="[1062,1219,656,680]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="354">A. squarrosae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Minor differences include the higher number of semiannuli between the coxae and the genital area and fewer striae on the genital coverflap of 
<taxonomicName box="[293,415,728,752]" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Aceria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Prostigmata" pageId="5" pageNumber="354" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="virgatae">
<emphasis box="[293,415,728,752]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="354">A. virgatae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in respect to 
<taxonomicName box="[564,720,728,752]" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Aceria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Prostigmata" pageId="5" pageNumber="354" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="squarrosae">
<emphasis box="[564,720,728,752]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="354">A. squarrosae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Finally, the coxal plates of 
<taxonomicName box="[1034,1156,728,752]" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Aceria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Prostigmata" pageId="5" pageNumber="354" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="virgatae">
<emphasis box="[1034,1156,728,752]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="354">A. virgatae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
